      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SAMMY SUFFARELL (11) drew very wide and had to race three deep without cover last start so prepared to forgive that result. Had won two in a row prior, one of them at this circuit and distance. If things go his way from the back row he could be back in the winners' list. Manners have let FLY TO THE FINISH NZ (6) down in both outings since recording a win at this circuit and distance but he has trialled nicely twice sine the last outing. He is up to winning this if he gets it right. ART IDEAL (8) was beaten as a hot favourite last time but did have work. Recorded a series of wins and placing prior, leading from a similar draw to this when scoring two back at this circuit and distance. Deserves another chance. TRUE GRIT NZ (7) draws wide but is in first four contention after scoring last start by 8 metres at this venue. ",
